# Morpheus.dev

**Tagline:** Build a backend before your backend exists.

Morpheus.dev is a visual mock-backend builder for developers. It allows users to define tables and schemas, generate realistic mock data, create relationships without writing SQL, expose live REST endpoints for development use, and later export the project structure toward a production-ready backend such as Supabase.

This document is the product definition, architecture spec, data model reference, MVP scope, and implementation guide for the first version of Morpheus.dev.

---

# 1. Product Summary

## 1.1 Core Idea
Developers often need a working backend before the real backend is ready. Today they patch together JSON files, ad hoc mock servers, temporary databases, Postman mocks, or quick Supabase setups.

Morpheus.dev solves that by letting developers:

- create tables visually
- define schema fields and constraints
- generate mock records
- define relationships between tables
- automatically expose REST endpoints
- connect the generated backend to their frontend or development environment in real time
- eventually export schema and seed structure to platforms like Supabase

## 1.2 Primary Outcome
The product should make it possible for a developer to go from nothing to a usable backend in minutes.

## 1.3 Core Value Proposition
> Spin up a working backend with real endpoints in under 2 minutes.

## 1.4 Target User
Primary users:

- frontend developers
- fullstack developers prototyping features
- solo builders
- startup teams building MVPs
- product engineers working ahead of backend readiness

Secondary users:

- QA engineers creating testable environments
- agencies prototyping client systems
- technical product teams validating workflows

---

# 2. Product Positioning

## 2.1 What Morpheus.dev Is
Morpheus.dev is a:

- visual mock backend builder
- schema-first development tool
- mock data generator
- live API runtime for frontend development
- bridge between prototype backend and future production backend

## 2.2 What Morpheus.dev Is Not
It is not initially:

- a full backend-as-a-service replacement
- a full ORM platform
- a general cloud hosting platform
- a production-grade auth and permissions layer
- an enterprise API gateway
- a generic no-code app builder

## 2.3 Positioning Statement
For developers who need a working backend before the real backend exists, Morpheus.dev provides a visual way to define data models, generate realistic data, and expose live APIs instantly, without requiring manual backend setup.

