# 5. User Stories

## 5.1 Core User Stories
- As a developer, I want to create tables and fields visually so I do not have to set up a database manually.
- As a developer, I want to generate mock rows so I can test my frontend with realistic data.
- As a developer, I want to define relationships between tables without writing SQL.
- As a developer, I want REST endpoints to be created automatically so I can connect my frontend immediately.
- As a developer, I want POST requests to create records so the mock backend behaves more like a real backend.
- As a developer, I want to inspect the generated data so I can verify it matches what I need.
- As a developer, I want to copy the live API URL and use it in my local environment quickly.
- As a developer, I want the schema to stay as the source of truth, so changes to my models update the backend structure consistently.

## 5.2 Future User Stories
- As a developer, I want to export the schema and seed setup to Supabase later.
- As a developer, I want to simulate edge cases like empty states and failure states later.
- As a developer, I want to preview generated SQL if I need more control later.

