# 9. Core System Components

## 9.1 Frontend App
The frontend handles all user interaction for project creation and backend modeling.

### Frontend modules
- Project Dashboard
- Project Workspace
- Schema Builder
- Table Editor
- Data Preview
- Endpoints Panel
- Relations Canvas
- Environment Panel

## 9.2 Builder API
The internal API used by the Morpheus frontend to manage project metadata.

Responsibilities:
- create and update projects
- create and update tables and fields
- define relationships
- trigger schema compilation
- trigger data generation
- read endpoint definitions
- expose environment config

## 9.3 Metadata Service
This is the main source of truth for project definitions.

Responsibilities:
- persist project metadata
- validate model structure
- expose metadata to compiler and runtime engine

## 9.4 Schema Compiler
The service that converts visual schema definitions into actual runtime SQL structures.

Responsibilities:
- validate schema integrity
- compute creation order
- compile SQL for runtime database
- rebuild runtime database when schema changes

## 9.5 Mock Data Generator
Generates records for each table according to field type and mock strategy.

Responsibilities:
- generate values by field type
- enforce simple uniqueness where applicable
- generate foreign key relationships correctly
- generate rows in dependency order

## 9.6 Runtime API Engine
Serves the actual API endpoints that the developer’s app will consume.

Responsibilities:
- resolve endpoint definitions by project
- execute SQL against the project runtime database
- validate request payloads
- return JSON responses

## 9.7 Export Adapter Layer
Future component.

Responsibilities:
- convert metadata into SQL migrations
- generate seed scripts
- produce Supabase-compatible export packages
- produce OpenAPI definitions

