# 13. Runtime Data Strategy

## 13.1 Runtime Storage Choice
Use one SQLite database file per project.

Example:
```text
/runtime-dbs/{projectId}.sqlite
```

## 13.2 Why SQLite per Project
- easy isolation
- cheap
- simple reset and regeneration
- easy file-based lifecycle
- good for development usage
- easier future export story

## 13.3 Runtime Table Creation
Tables are created dynamically based on schema metadata.

Example generated SQL:

```sql
CREATE TABLE users (
  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  first_name TEXT NOT NULL,
  email TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE
);

CREATE TABLE orders (
  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id TEXT NOT NULL,
  total_amount REAL NOT NULL,
  FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(id)
);
```

---

# 14. Internal JSON Contract

The metadata engine should be able to serialize a project to an internal JSON representation like this:

```json
{
  "project": {
    "name": "Demo Shop",
    "slug": "demo-shop"
  },
  "tables": [
    {
      "name": "users",
      "fields": [
        { "name": "id", "type": "uuid", "primaryKey": true },
        { "name": "first_name", "type": "string", "required": true, "mockStrategy": "firstName" },
        { "name": "email", "type": "email", "required": true, "unique": true, "mockStrategy": "email" }
      ],
      "rowCountTarget": 100
    },
    {
      "name": "orders",
      "fields": [
        { "name": "id", "type": "uuid", "primaryKey": true },
        { "name": "user_id", "type": "uuid", "required": true },
        { "name": "total_amount", "type": "float", "required": true, "mockStrategy": "price" }
      ],
      "rowCountTarget": 300
    }
  ],
  "relationships": [
    {
      "sourceTable": "orders",
      "sourceField": "user_id",
      "targetTable": "users",
      "targetField": "id",
      "type": "many_to_one"
    }
  ]
}
```

This internal JSON contract should become a foundational abstraction for:
- schema compilation
- runtime generation
- export logic
- future import/export support

