# 22. Validation and Guardrails

## 22.1 Schema Validation Rules
- table names must be unique within a project
- field names must be unique within a table
- each table must have one primary key
- relationship types must use compatible field types
- required fields must not use invalid default values
- enum values must not be empty when type is enum

## 22.2 Runtime Validation Rules
- POST body must match defined field schema
- unique fields should reject duplicates
- required fields should reject missing values
- foreign key fields should validate referenced existence where practical

---

