# 28. Short Internal Summary for Claude / Cursor

Morpheus.dev is a developer tool that creates a working mock backend from a visual schema. Users create projects, define tables and fields, generate mock data, define relationships, and automatically get live REST endpoints that can be consumed by their frontend during development. The system must separate metadata from runtime data. Metadata lives in PostgreSQL. Runtime records live in SQLite per project. The frontend is React + TypeScript. The backend is Fastify + TypeScript. The MVP focuses on table creation, schema definition, mock data generation, relationships, and GET/POST endpoints. Export to Supabase and advanced canvas workflows come later.

