# Usage Tracking & Metering

## Purpose

The system must include a built-in usage tracking layer to monitor resource consumption per project. This is required for:

- enforcing usage limits (free vs paid tiers)
- preventing abuse
- enabling monetization
- understanding infrastructure costs

Usage tracking is a core architectural requirement and must not be treated as an optional feature.

---

## What Must Be Tracked

### API Requests

Track all runtime API calls per project.

Requirements:
- total request count
- count per endpoint
- count per HTTP method (GET, POST, etc.)
- timestamps for usage periods

```ts
type ApiUsage = {
  projectId: string
  totalRequests: number
  requestsByEndpoint: Record<string, number>
  requestsByMethod: Record<string, number>
  periodStart: string
  periodEnd: string
}